ault-300x163.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 618px) 100vw, 618px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>You can customize the message shown to visitors by clicking the <b>Edit<\/b> button at the top of the page and then on the name or description to update the message.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/07\/broadcast_message_edit.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-827\" alt=\"Edit screen share broadcast page message\" src=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/07\/broadcast_message_edit.png\" width=\"620\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/07\/broadcast_message_edit.png 620w, https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/07\/broadcast_message_edit-300x219.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Click the\u00a0<b>Update<\/b>\u00a0button when you are done to save your changes.\u00a0If you are a user on a Premium Account, you will also have the option of customizing the messages that are shown to visitors when you are in the middle of a restricted or locked broadcast (see next week&#8217;s blog entry for more details).<\/p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 48px;\"><b>Ideas For Use<\/b><\/p>\n<p>You can use the broadcast page message to further engage your visitors:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Contact Information<\/b> &#8211; Put your contact info so that your visitors will know how to get in touch when you are not broadcasting.<\/li>\n<li><b>Simple Meeting Scheduling<\/b> &#8211; After you schedule a presentation, update your broadcast page message with information about the presentation so that viewers who show up early will know that they are in the right place.<\/li>\n<li><b>Supplementary Materials<\/b> &#8211; Include links to supplementary materials (such as white papers) that your viewers can review after seeing your presentation.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 48px;\"><b>What\u2019s Next<\/b><\/p>\n<p>Next week, we will cover two additional broadcasting features that we just released: broadcast restriction (the ability to restrict a broadcasts to viewers with an access code that you specify) and broadcast locking (the ability to lock an active broadcast to prevent new viewers from joining).<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>About a year ago, we launched our broadcasting feature, which made it possible for you to share your screen to a handle that you select (i.e., http:\/\/www.screenleap.com\/your_company).\u00a0Viewers can view your broadcast simply by going to your broadcast page.\u00a0When you are not actively broadcasting, your broadcast page serves to welcome your visitors: previously, a visitor would [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[94,199,93,96],"class_list":["post-820","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-screenleap","tag-contact-information","tag-screenleap","tag-simple-meeting-scheduling","tag-supplementary-materials-include"],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/820","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=820"}],"version-history":[{"count":48,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/820\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":887,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\